pageContext.claim: “Despite so many positive events and victories, Media Research Center reports that 92% of stories on Donald Trump are negative on ABC, CBS and ABC. It is FAKE NEWS! Don’t worry, the Failing New York Times didn’t even put the Brett Kavanaugh victory on the Front Page yesterday-A17!”
pageContext.analysis: Negative coverage doesn't equate to "fake news," as Trump suggests. Kavanaugh was not on the front page of the Times on Oct. 9, but the confirmation did lead the paper on Oct. 6 when he was confirmed and Oct. 10 for his first day on the bench. Plus, the Times is not "failing." The paper has seen spikes subscribers since Trump took office.
